      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(test-env): exclude browser cache subdirs when staging .gemini into temp home",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n`copyDirIfExists` used `fs.cpSync({ recursive: true })` with no filter. When staging `.gemini` into the temp test home, it copied the entire directory including multi-GB browser cache/profile subdirectories, causing ENOSPC in CI.\n\n## Fix\n\n- `copyDirIfExists` gains an `excludeDirs` option that filters matching subdirectories\n- Added `LIVE_EXTERNAL_AUTH_EXCLUDE_SUBDIRS` list (cache, Code Cache, GPUCache, Service Worker, IndexedDB, Session Storage, Local Storage, DawnGraphiteCache, DawnWebGPUCache, ShaderCache, GrShaderCache, Crashpad)\n- `.gemini` staging now passes the exclude list\n- Added regression test\n\n## Files changed\n- `test/test-env.ts` — filter option, exclude list, staging update\n- `test/test-env.test.ts` — new test, `os` import\n\n## Testing\n\n```\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/test-env.test.ts\n```\n\nAll 5 tests pass (4 existing + 1 new).\n\nCloses #91893",
        "branch": "fix/91893-test-env-copydir-size-guard",
